<hr>
<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br><br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br><br>
A description of the source can be added if clarity is needed, at the end of the Works Cited entry.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	&#34;Title of Image.&#34; <em>Title of source</em>, date or year of publication, URL. Description. 
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of image">An Offering to the Ocean in La Punta, Peru.</span>&#34;
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of source">Sydney Morning Herald</span></em>,
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">19 May. 2009</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="URL">www.smh.com.au/snapshots/</span>.
	<span class="hover" title="Description">Web image</span>.
</blockquote>
<br><br>
If the image was obtained from a website, place the name of the website as the publisher after the title of the image. Do not italicise the name of the publisher.
<br><br>
